DESCRIPTION:

Featuring high-quality wildlife and landscape photography, Facing the Atlantic is an extraordinary journey through Western Europe and the land facing the Atlantic beginning with the Azores and ending in Iceland.
EPISODE GUIDE

FACING THE ATLANTIC: Episode 1
The journey begins in the volcanic Azores archipelago, where the waters are home to sperm whales, sharks and giant devil rays.

FACING THE ATLANTIC: Episode 2
As the journey continues through France to Britain, meet the world's largest squirrel, an unusual blonde hedgehog, and some lost birds.

FACING THE ATLANTIC: Episode 3
Scotland and Iceland are home to breathtaking landscapes, beavers and fish which thrive near volcanic vents
